During a press briefing, Secretary of Education Dr. Miguel Cardona discussed the administration's focus on safely reopening schools. He announced that all 50 states, D.C., and Puerto Rico will receive nearly $122 billion from the American Rescue Plan to help reopen schools. Additionally, an additional $10 billion will be allocated for states to conduct screening and surveillance testing in schools. Cardona also announced a National Reopening Summit for schools to share best practices on reopening safely. Dr. Jill Biden and Dr. Rochelle Walensky will be in attendance. Cardona emphasized the importance of in-person learning and encouraged educators to get vaccinated. He also discussed the use of funds to support students and address achievement and opportunity gaps. In response to questions, Cardona highlighted the need for transparent reporting on how the funds are used and addressed concerns about the reopening of schools and vaccine hesitancy among teachers. The press secretary, Jen Psaki, also addressed various topics including Russia recalling its ambassador, violence against Asian Americans, tax filing deadlines, press access to border facilities, and the President's remarks on taxes and democracy. She reiterated the administration's commitment to transparency and addressing the root causes of migration at the border.